sec.p:
The terms used to describe the study population differed across studies:
‘Black African’ (Thomas, Saleem, and Abraham [28]; Barter‐Godfrey and Taket [11]; Bamidele et al. [14]);
‘Black Caribbean’ (Barter‐Godfrey and Taket [11]; Thomas, Saleem, and Abraham [28]);
‘Afro‐Caribbean/African’ (Bell et al. [21]; Kernohan [20]) and
‘Blacks’ (Atri et al. [13]; Offman et al. [12]; Pfeffer [29]).
